8.

	a)
	
	All visible lines are length 1, lines from vertices to each station also length one.
	
	Equilateral Triangles. Height = sqrt(3) / 2. 
	opp = hyp * sin theta
		= sin theta
		= sin 60.
	Therefore dist from A to B = sqrt(3)
		
	b)
	
	Dist = 1.5.
	Line from C to intersection of all hexes = 1.
	Dist from intersection to line segment = 1/2 line length = .5.
	
	-> Dist = 1.5.
	
9.

	a) 
	
	min sensor range for every pair to communicate: r = sqrt(2)
	
	b)
	
	Orient each such that it is looking at it's neighbor. Networks can communicate cyclically
	
	c)
	
	Angle such that each sensor is pointing directly at the opposite corner, with pi/4 range to the left and right.
	This requires r to be sqrt(2)
	
	d)
	
	No orientation with angle less than pi/2 will allow a complete network. Each node must be able to communicate with ALL OTHER nodes.
	
10.

	a)
	
	First Antenna, place it such that it's range is perfectly along one of the edges.
	Place second such that it is on the opposite side of the square, positioned at the maximum position of the first's range.
		Angle second so that it is facing towards First with minimal overlap.
		
	This puts two triangles with acute angles of 45 degrees, and side lengths one.
		This means they have base lengths of: sqrt(2)/2km
		This means they together have an area of (2*(1)*(sqrt(2)/2))km^2
			Area = sqrt(2)km^2
			
		Duplicate this structure with the remaining area. 
		
		Now covering a total area of 2*sqrt(2) km^2. This is greater than the area of the square, which is 1 km^2. 
		
